The prices in (15) are set as expected values of future cash flows to the shareholders conditional on the information available to them; what someone is willing to pay for a share depends on his expected payoff from owning that share. Given the possibility of a liquidity shock, a shareholder cannot be sure of holding the share until the terminal date. This means that the shareholder’s expected payoff differs from the firm’s expected terminal cash flow; it also depends on the possible trading losses the shareholder could incur, given a liquidity shock prior to the terminal date. The price at
