We are thinking of the representative of shareholders as the board of directors (who own stock) or a large “inside” shareholder. We can either assume that the contract they write for the manager is unobservable to the market (and hence to small shareholders and nonowners) or observable. We prefer the unobservability assumption because it corresponds to actual practice. In this case, the optimal contract involves
